            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1381402309,
            "creation_date": 1381228568,
            "body": "<p>So I ended up finding the answer.  I needed to add a <code>p.nextline()<\/code> above the for loop to get it to properly read the next line of code.  Thanks for all the help to everyone.  Your answers were greatly appreciated.<\/p>\n\n<p>Apparently, what nextline does is it grabs the remainder of the current line, outputs that to whatever (if anything) you have it equal to, and move the pointer to the next line.  That's why I was having issues. <\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 19245395,
